    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nCurrently, since the introduction of #9113 the line number will be highlighted according to the `numhl` attribute (if set).\r\nHowever, I think it would make more sense to only overwrite the `LineNr` but *not* the `CursorLineNr` highlight groups because in use cases like (e.g. [vim-gitgutter](https://github.com/airblade/vim-gitgutter)) where long areas may be highlighted with `numhl` attributes, the `CursorLineNr` highlighting would provide useful information.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThus, I propose to either not overwrite `CursorLineNr` with the `numhl` attribute by default or at least provide a configuration option to achieve this behavior.\r\n",
